Sentence: These measure- ments suggest type-II superconductivity in TaOs with superconducting transition temperature T c = 2.07 K.

In this work, we report the detailed characterization of the NCS superconductor TaOs exhibiting bulk super- conductivity at T c = 2.07 K. Superconducting properties were determined by the magnetic susceptibility, electrical resistiv- ity, and specific heat measurements.
The specific heat data in figure 3 confirms bulk superconductivity in TaOs.
